# Web App Conventions

## Component Patterns
- Server components by default. Use `'use client'` only when React hooks or browser APIs are needed.
- CSS Modules co-located with components (e.g., `Header.module.css` next to `Header.tsx`).
- BEM-inspired naming within CSS modules. No Tailwind utility classes.
- Prefer CSS custom properties for theming over component-level style props.

## File Organization
- Pages: `apps/web/src/app/<route>/page.tsx`
- Components: `apps/web/src/components/<domain>/` (e.g., `home/`, `layout/`, `shared/`)
- Content data: `apps/web/src/lib/content/` (static registries, copy)
- Sanity integration: `apps/web/src/sanity/` (client, queries, types)
- SEO utilities: `apps/web/src/lib/seo/`
- Hooks: `apps/web/src/hooks/`
- Types: `apps/web/src/types/`

## Styling Rules
- All colors, spacing tokens, and font stacks defined as CSS custom properties in `globals.css`.
- Depth-zone-specific overrides use `html[data-home-depth]` attribute selectors.
- Use `clamp()` for responsive values. Avoid magic breakpoint numbers when possible.
- Transitions should use shared timing variables (`--depth-transition`, `--depth-ease`) on the homepage.
- `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` — disable non-essential animations.

## Content & SEO
- Static marketing content in `lib/content/beringia-static.ts` — single source of truth for homepage copy.
- Solutions registry in `lib/content/solutions.ts` — drives `/solutions` and `/solutions/[slug]`.
- Insights have a canonical registry — no duplicate mock arrays.
- Use shared route helpers for URLs; keep JSON-LD aligned with route slugs and canonical URLs.
